data.description: ***GET SNOWED IN*** Come home to this majestic Hudson Valley property and be settled in to enjoy the breathtaking sunsets! Perfectly nestled in the Shawangunk Valley foothills surrounded by sprawling organic and "pick your own" farms, beholds this charming 1960's Brick Sugar Maple Split primed and ready for a new owner. Nestled on the highly sought after and tranquil Forest Glen Road, this home is perfect all year round with walking access to the Hudson Valley Rail Trail. Scenic trail walks into town (Gardiner/New Paltz), bike rides and even snow shoeing for miles awaits! This beautiful home has been freshly painted and features oak flooring finished with walnut oil, an updated kitchen that boasts butcher block countertops and stainless steel appliances. The property features over an acre of parklike landscape including a private backyard perfect for family BBQ's, large gatherings, and gardening. Spacious finished lower level featuring two large rooms, laundry area and space for a second bathroom. Plenty of room for storage in the attached 2 car garage and oversized breezeway with soaring ceilings allowing great natural lighting. Conveniently located close to the Minnewaska State Park, Gardiner, New Paltz, High Falls, Rosendale and Stone Ridge. Nearby also awaits locally sourced restaurants, wineries, breweries, cideries, world renowned rock climbing, hiking, year round outdoor activities, shops, and live entertainment. Home is sold "AS IS" and has to be toured to fully appreciate all that is being offered. Call today  to schedule a private tour!
